    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 7 @ 2023/2024",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Which of these prevents overloading of electric circuits?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "Fuses",
        "voltage",
        "current",
        "capacitor"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Fuses"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>Fuses are designed to break the circuit if the current exceeds a safe level, preventing overloading. Voltage, current, and capacitors do not serve this protective function.</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
