    "name": "Question 14 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Which of these prevent overloading of electric circuits?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "Fuses",
        "Voltage",
        "Current",
        "Capacitor"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Fuses"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>Fuses are safety devices designed to melt and break the circuit when current exceeds a safe value, preventing overloading. Voltage and current are circuit parameters, while capacitors store energy but don't prevent overloads.</p>"
    },
